# Purpose: Audit OpenSchool pages for WCAG 2.1 AA compliance.

You are performing an accessibility audit on OpenSchool. Check each HTML page
against the following criteria and report findings.

## Audit Checklist

### Perceivable
- [ ] All images have meaningful `alt` text (or `alt=""` for decorative)
- [ ] Color is not the only means of conveying information
- [ ] Contrast ratios meet 4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text
- [ ] Text can be resized to 200% without loss of content
- [ ] `prefers-reduced-motion` media query is respected

### Operable
- [ ] All functionality available via keyboard
- [ ] No keyboard traps
- [ ] Skip-link present and functional
- [ ] Focus indicators visible (`.focus-visible` styles)
- [ ] Focus order follows logical reading order
- [ ] Modal focus trapping works correctly

### Understandable
- [ ] `lang` attribute on `<html>`
- [ ] Form inputs have associated `<label>` elements
- [ ] Error messages are descriptive and linked via `aria-describedby`
- [ ] Consistent navigation across pages

### Robust
- [ ] Valid HTML (run through W3C validator)
- [ ] ARIA roles and properties used correctly
- [ ] `aria-live` regions for dynamic content (toast, status)
- [ ] `role="dialog"` + `aria-modal="true"` on modals
- [ ] Interactive elements use correct semantic elements (`<button>`, `<a>`)

## How to Report

For each issue found, report:
1. **Page**: Which HTML file
2. **Element**: CSS selector or description
3. **Issue**: What's wrong
4. **WCAG Criterion**: e.g., 1.4.3 Contrast
5. **Fix**: Suggested remediation

## Automated Checks

Also recommend running:
- `npx axe-core` (npm install @axe-core/cli)
- `npx pa11y <url>` (npm install pa11y)
- Lighthouse accessibility audit in Chrome DevTools
